https://punchng.com/akinkuotu-bows-out-as-nama-md-pwajok-takes-over/Okechukwu Nnodim 
Published 13 January 2022

Capt. Fola Akinkuotu has completed his five-year tenure as the managing director of the Nigerian Airspace Management Agency, while the Federal Government on Wednesday asked Mr. Matthew Pwajok to oversee the agency pending the appointment of a substantive chief executive officer.
The appointment of Pwajok was conveyed in a letter from the Federal Ministry of Aviation marked FMA/ PS/ APPT/CEO/014/1/23 and addressed to the managing director/CEO of NAMA.
The Director, Human Resources, FMA, S. D. Muhammad, signed the letter on behalf of the Minister of Aviation, Hadi Sirika.
The letter read in part, “I am directed to inform you that the minister has approved that Mr. Pwajok, Mathew Lawrence, Director of Operations, to oversee the office of the Managing Director/CEO pending the appointment of a substantive MD/CEO.” 
The minister said in the letter that Pwajok should be accorded the all the necessary support and cooperation he needs while overseeing the office. Read Also Flight delays: Air traffic controllers suspend strike, meet NCAA DG todayControllers’ shortage hits NAMA, agency engages non-technical staff, retireesNAMA trains, certifies 24 new air traffic controllers 
In a similar development, Sirika also approved the appointment and deployment of directors and special assistants to his office, the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria, NAMA, and the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority.
The appointments and deployments were contained in a letter dated January 12, 2022, which was addressed to the chief executives of NCAA, NAMA and FAAN, with reference FMA/PS/APPT/CEO/014/1/21.









